reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on July 18, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars received a faulty set, but the seller made it right.
reviews.reviewText: UPDATE: the seller has contacted me and we are working through a resolution. Once I receive the replacement product, I’ll update my review.UPDATE 2: I received the replacement today. This one is fully functional so based on this I’ve updated my review to reflect the quality and the excellent customer service the seller demonstrated. The compression features of these are great, I was able to fit two in a travel backpack. Out of my first order I was able to use one of the cubes on my recent vacation and I could easily fit 7 bathing suits in one of the mediums.The true test will be how these replacements hold up and I look forward to using them on my next trip.———————————————————————Searched high and low for the perfect cubes and thought I’d found them. The design of these are great but the quality isn’t there. The zipper on 2 of the cubes weren’t even functional so they can’t be used. I had to make due with the ones that did work since my trip is this weekend. The compression design is awesome but these aren’t made sturdy enough to actually hold up to their purpose.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on September 27, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 3.0 out of 5 stars Zipper broke with first use
reviews.reviewText: I'm giving these 3 stars because I did end up using them. This came with 4 adorable pouches, I love the design.3 of them are space savers with 2 zippers. One zipper us to close it, the 2nd zipper goes around the perimeter and "flattens" the clothing items.However, when I was packing, before even leaving for my trip, the perimeter zipper broke on one (I had not over stuffed it).I also found they really don't compress and space save like other brands. These are more of just an organizational packing system, in my opinion.I tried many folding styles to see how to maximize the amount of clothes in each bag. I found folding the clothing item flat, the size of the bag, and stacking them in the bag worked better than rolling.They're not very durable. But they did hold a lot of my clothes and it was nice to have my items organized in my luggage.I wouldn't buy these again, I'd find a more durable set that actually compresses, but these are cute.
